  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to be sure that no one can recover my account without knowing the valid password of my account.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: It is possible to recover an account by entering a valid Passphrase and invalid Password. \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\n\r\nIt should not be possible. \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\n\r\nStatus recovers the account associated with a Passphrase without checking if the Password is valid.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status on 2 separate devices (A and B)\r\n- Note the seed phrase of A\r\n- Navigate to the \"I already have an account\" menu of B\r\n- Enter the Passphrase of A\r\n- Enter some random password, not the one you've chosen when you created your A account\r\n\r\nYou can find a recording of my workflow here: https://youtu.be/zrNvnYzxqwo \r\n - As you can see, the initial password for my account is \"qqq111\" and then I use \"somerandompass\" when recovering it\r\n - The both devices have the same account when comparing the contact code associated with them\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: 0.9.21 (6129), Nightly build \"June 27\", http://artifacts.status.im:8081/artifactory/nightlies-local/im.status.ethereum-d276d5-n-fl.apk\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Android or iOS.)\r\n* Operating System: Tested on Android. Can't confirm about iOS.\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\n\r\nhttps://gist.github.com/GeorgiG/25a56a33d6ccaa203c8ac2be4aac1558\n\n<blockquote><img src=\"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zrNvnYzxqwo/maxresdefault.jpg\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div><img src=\"/yts/img/favicon_144-vfliLAfaB.png\" height=\"14\"> YouTube</div><div><strong><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zrNvnYzxqwo\">Recover an account</a></strong></div><div> </div></blockquote>\n<blockquote></blockquote>\n<blockquote><img src=\"https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/5781465?s=400&v=4\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div><img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/favicon.ico\" height=\"14\"> Gist</div><div><strong><a href=\"https://gist.github.com/GeorgiG/25a56a33d6ccaa203c8ac2be4aac1558\">Recover an account</a></strong></div><div>GitHub is where people build software. More than 28 million people use GitHub to discover, fork, and contribute to over 85 million projects.</div></blockquote>",
